{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "64c0e7bb6f5bfc7ab78ae766", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d7713c52ffa3c944600e3"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9e"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "61a8bf0fc821b6514e527d78", "title": "BITSAT 2014", "isVisible": true}], "position": 0, "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 1, "approximateTimeRequired": 60, "question": {"text": "A narrow beam of protons and deuterons, each having the same momentum, enters a region of uniform magnetic field directed perpendicular to their direction of momentum. The ratio of the radii of the circular paths described by them is", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "JMt3H", "text": "1: 2", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "ttCTw", "text": "1: 1", "isCorrect": true, "image": null}, {"id": "0ykPW", "text": "2: 1", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}, {"id": "ULwlR", "text": "1: 3", "isCorrect": false, "image": null}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "Since, the radius of circular path of a charged\r\n\r\nparticle in magnetic field is $\\mathrm{r}=\\frac{\\mathrm{mv}}{\\mathrm{qB}}=\\frac{\\rho}{\\mathrm{qB}}$\r\n\r\nNow, the radius of circular path of charged particle of given momentum $\\rho$ and magnetic field $\\mathrm{B}$ is given by $\\mathrm{r} \\propto \\frac{1}{\\mathrm{q}}$\r\n\r\nBut charge on both charged particles, protons and deuterons, is same. Therefore,\r\n\r\n$$\r\n\r\n\\frac{\\mathrm{r}_{\\mathrm{p}}}{\\mathrm{r}_{\\mathrm{D}}}=\\frac{\\mathrm{q}_{\\mathrm{D}}}{\\mathrm{q}_{\\rho}}=\\frac{1}{\\mathrm{l}}\r\n\r\n$$", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "questionLabels": [], "__v": 0, "masterId": "MOGBSPYQ59420479", "bucket": "", "category": null, "microConcepts": [], "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperT